data.title: Socialist Party of Lithuania
data.meta_description: The Socialist Party of Lithuania was a left-wing political party in Lithuania. It was founded on March 26, 1994, and briefly had a Member of the Seimas in 1996. It did not achieve any success in elections and merged with the Front Party in 2009 to form the Socialist People's Front.
